Package: moses
Type: Package
Title: Multi Objective Sequence Splitter
Version: 0.1.4
Date: 2025-01-30
Authors@R: c(person("Felipe", "Campelo",
    email   = "fcampelo@gmail.com",
    role    = c("aut", "cre")))
Maintainer: Felipe Campelo <fcampelo@gmail.com>
Description: A tool for splitting sequence data (or other types of 
             potentially imbalanced data with dependence structures) 
             based on the simultaneous optimisation of multiple 
             objectives, including split sizes, consistency of class 
             balances, and within-split diversity.
License: GPL-2
Depends: R (>= 4.4.0)
Imports: assertthat (>= 0.2.1),
         dplyr (>= 1.1.4),
         BiocManager (>= 1.30.25),
         pbapply (>= 1.7.0),
         seqinr (>= 4.2.0),
         rlang (>= 1.1.4),
         tidyr (>= 1.3.1),
         fastcluster (>= 1.2.6)
Suggests: Biostrings (>= 2.60.0),
          CellaRepertorium (>= 1.8.0)
SuggestsNote:
  BioC (>= 3.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
URL: https://github.com/fcampelo/moses/
